    "body": "Problem:\r\nWhen enabling oxfmt and checking it's status via \":checkhealth vim.lsp\", the following errors are printed:\r\n- ⚠️ WARNING Unknown filetype 'javascript.jsx' (Hint: filename extension != filetype).\r\n- ⚠️ WARNING Unknown filetype 'typescript.tsx' (Hint: filename extension != filetype).\r\n- ⚠️ WARNING Unknown filetype 'handlebars' (Hint: filename extension != filetype).\r\n- ⚠️ WARNING Unknown filetype 'hbs' (Hint: filename extension != filetype).\r\n- ⚠️ WARNING Unknown filetype 'mdx' (Hint: filename extension != filetype).\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\nRemove unknown filetypes from oxfmt config",
    "closed_at": "2026-02-25T22:27:29Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thanks. The problem with those warnings is that they don't know about potentially third-party filetypes. E.g. `handlebars` is provided by https://github.com/nono/vim-handlebars\r\n\r\nPlease only remove the filetypes that you are certain are invalid.",
            "created_at": "2026-02-25T18:28:55Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/4325#issuecomment-3961184399",
            "id": 3961184399,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/4325",
